analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Fragile Neutrality Amid Volatility Expansion. The GMS 47/100 dictates a neutral posture as the regime faces volatility expansion with the VIX surging to 22.07. Credit spread decompression in high-yield assets and the erosion of digital sentiment signal a localized liquidity drain. While net liquidity remains high, the compression of commodity proxies highlights a waning growth-inflation reflex. The fiscal-monetary nexus remains precarious, necessitating capital preservation as tail-risk convexity increases. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
